                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>Instead of selling the app upfront and losing the possibility of selling more services in the future, Julie decides to have the schools she is targeting \"pay as they go\" by paying for the active number of students using the apps per month. This way, they don't have to invest a big amount of money upfront and would maintain an ongoing relationship with Julie's company.</h5>",
