                    {
                        "unit_id": 2863,
                        "title": "Key Revenue Streams used in Businesses",
                        "slug": "key-revenue-streams-used-in-businesses",
                        "order": 80,
                        "status": "publish",
                        "content": "",
                        "media": {
                            "youtube_video_id": null,
                            "banner_image_url": null,
                            "featured_image_url": null,
                            "pdf_template_url": null
                        },
                        "meta": {
                            "course-unit-read": "",
                            "course-unit-read-more": "",
                            "course-unit-quotes": "",
                            "course-unit-case-study": "<h5>The key revenue stream that Julie wants to use for her app is a subscription model where schools pay $2 per student per month. Given the number of schools in her district and the number of students that they have between the age of 10-13 years, Julie estimates that if she gets 10% of those students to sign up, she could have 10,000 subscriptions by the end of the year, resulting in $20,000 per month of revenue.</h5>",
